FRONTLINE ROADS v0.32.12 FINAL AUDIT

Scope
- Remove the gameplay camera controls from the tactical-map overlay layer.
- Preserve zoom, selected-base focus and player-position focus behavior.
- Validate civilization-level combat pressure with production systems rather than a display-only enemy count.
- Keep v0.32.11 dense-front constants unless measured playtests show a balance defect.

HUD correction
- gameMapControls is a direct hudHeader grid item.
- The gameplay controls no longer carry the generic mapControls overlay class.
- Normal, portrait and low-height landscape layouts place the controls beside the base summary.
- position:absolute, right-edge anchoring and bottom anchoring are absent from gameplay camera controls.
- The base summary truncates safely instead of pushing the controls over the map or context panel.
- Buttons remain available for zoom in, zoom out, selected base focus and player-position focus.

Balance harness
- Uses production CombatSystem, WaveSystem, routing, defenses, repairs and city-defeat recovery.
- Nine-front radial road network with enemy bases 360m from the city.
- Seven deterministic scenarios, each simulating ten game minutes.
- Civilization levels 1 through 4 with standard, underbuilt and fortified defense profiles.
- Records total and moving enemy density, kills, waves, destroyed defenses, repair load, city HP and city defeats.

Measured results
- standard-civ1: peak 24 enemies, average 13.2 moving, 0 destroyed defenses, city HP minimum 100.
- standard-civ2: peak 64 enemies, average 41.0 moving, 0 destroyed defenses, 702.2 HP repaired, city HP minimum 100.
- underbuilt-civ3: peak 193 enemies, average 127.4 moving, 9 destroyed defenses, city HP minimum 67.
- standard-civ3: peak 176 enemies, average 119.5 moving, 3 destroyed defenses, city HP minimum 100.
- underbuilt-civ4: peak 357 enemies, average 195.3 moving, 17 destroyed defenses, city HP minimum 10, 1 city defeat.
- standard-civ4: peak 322 enemies, average 182.1 moving, 4 destroyed defenses, city HP minimum 100.
- fortified-civ4: peak 296 enemies, average 199.4 moving, 2 destroyed defenses, city HP minimum 100.
- All declared scenario checks passed.
- Dense-front constants remain unchanged because the measured progression differentiates stable, pressured and collapsing defenses.

